###################################
##          Instructions         ##
###################################

To reproduce the results shown in the manual, the following steps should be
taken in the Unix shell:

Extract the SoftSUSY version 3.5.1 [1] package file, which is available on 
the web under [2], and compile it (as given in the instructions on [2]):
  $ tar xvfz softsusy-3.5.1.tar.gz
  $ cd softsusy-3.5.1/
  $ ./configure
  $ make

Create a link to the executable `softpoint.x' somewhere in the PATH environment 
variable, e.g.:
  $ ln -s "$PWD/softpoint.x" ~/bin/softpoint.x
or
  $ sudo ln -s "$PWD/softpoint.x" /usr/local/bin/softpoint.x
Alternatively, one can replace the `softpoint.x' in th example scan definition
file with the absolute path the file `softpoint.x'.

Analogously, extract the SPheno version 3.3.3 [3] package file obtained from 
the web page [4] and compile it (as given in the instructions on [4]):
  $ tar xvfz SPheno-3.3.3.tar.gz
  $ cd SPheno-3.3.3
  $ make
and link the SPheno executable
  $ ln -s "$PWD/bin/SPheno" ~/bin/SPheno
or
  $ sudo ln -s "$PWD/bin/SPheno" /usr/local/bin/SPheno
or replace the part in the example scan definition file with its absolute path.

References
[1] B.C. Allanach,  [arXiv:hep-ph/0104145]
[2] http://softsusy.hepforge.org/
[3] W. Porod and F. Staub,  [arXiv:1104.1573]
[4] https://spheno.hepforge.org/
